Summary: The document provides the timetable for the MTech in Artificial Intelligence Systems course for the AY2024/2025 semester 1 intake. The course manager is Gary Zhenzhen and the course will run from August to November 2024. Classes will be held from Monday to Friday, from 9:00am to 5:30pm, with the exception of Wednesdays. The course includes modules on Intelligent Reasoning Systems, Machine Reasoning, and Cognitive Systems. The timetable is confidential and was last updated on 19 March 2025.

This document outlines the timetable for the MTech AIS (Master of Technology in Artificial Intelligence and Systems) course for the academic year 2024/2025. The course will begin on September 9, 2024 and will run from Monday to Friday, 9:00am to 5:00pm. The course will cover topics such as problem solving using pattern recognition, pattern recognition and machine learning systems, and intelligent sensing and sense making. The course manager for these classes is Fangming, and the course is part of the ISY5002 Graduate Certificate in Pattern Recognition Systems. This information is confidential and was last updated on March 19, 2025.

The AY2024/2025 Semester 1 Exam Timetable for the MTech AIS program includes exams for various graduate certificates such as Analytics Project Management, Intelligent Reasoning Systems, and Architecting Scalable Systems. The exams will take place from November 4 to 7, with each exam starting at 6:30pm and ending at 10:00pm. The document also includes a disclaimer that exam dates may be subject to change and that the timetable was last updated on March 19, 2025.
